The paper deals with the problem of haze removal or dehazing, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR). The authors also mention the use of traditional image quality metrics such as PSNR, SSIM, and CIEDE2000, which are commonly used in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) research. Finally, the paper compares state-of-the-art dehazing techniques, which may involve machine learning (cs.LG) approaches.
